{
  "text": "During periods of heavy rainfalls aquatic plant development is favoured, which may constitute a danger of flooding to adjacent areas and cause scarp landslides. During low flow periods, strongly developed plants may as well result in the deterioration of oxygen balance in a river due to decay processes caused by the decomposition of dead plant remains occurring in the bottom [CITATION_1] . This influences the deterioration of ecological quality of the watercourse.",
